GM's EYES ONLY: What Really Happened to the Dragon Soul
(This scene happens concurrently while the party is on the mound. Do not read this aloud. This is your guide for what happened to Bjorn.)
Down at the edge of the ruined village, Old Bjorn is calming his horses. He sees the brilliant streak of light—the dragon's soul—erupt from the mound. He watches, mesmerized, as it arcs down, a falling star of pure energy that streaks directly towards him.
He has no time to react. The soul strikes the cart, passing through the wood like smoke, and slams into his chest.
The impact is brutally physical. It feels like being kicked by a horse, throwing him back against the cart and knocking the wind from his lungs. For a moment, he blacks out.
When consciousness returns, it is to a world of agony. A white-hot fire courses through his veins. It feels like every bone in his 68-year-old body is being snapped and reset. His muscles tear and seize, spasming uncontrollably. A lifetime of aches, old injuries, and the simple wear of age are being scoured away by a brutal, cellular alchemy. A roar echoes in his mind—a sound of immense power and ancient loneliness, a missing piece of his own soul returning home with the force of a tidal wave.
He grits his teeth, his body convulsing in the dirt, stifling a scream of pure, agonizing pain. This lasts for ten seconds.
Then, it stops.
The pain recedes to a deep, throbbing ache. He pushes himself to his feet, his body trembling. He feels... different. The chronic pain in his lower back is gone. The stiffness in his knuckles has vanished. He feels stronger, more vital than he has in thirty years. He doesn't understand what just happened, only that it was terrifying, painful, and has fundamentally changed him.
Fearing he's been cursed or that the others will think him mad, he makes a choice: he will keep this to himself. He leans against the cart, struggling to catch his breath and compose his features, just as he hears the footsteps of the party returning down the hill.

